<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Bench-Triceps-Dip">Bench Triceps Dip</h3>



<p>As the name implies, this exercise predominantly targets the tricep muscles in your arms. However, it also targets your <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36293792/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">anterior deltoid</a> <sup>[3]</sup> and the pec muscles of your chest. Follow these simple steps below to get the most out of this workout.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Tricep Dip On Bench" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1000679739?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Bench Triceps Dip Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Sit on a flat bench with your hands gripping the edge and fingers pointed forward.</li>



<li>Place your feet flat on the ground, hip-width apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>With your hips off the bench, lower your body until your elbows are bent to about 90 degrees. Make sure to keep your back close to the bench.</li>



<li>Push up through your palms until you return to the starting position. Repeat the exercise. &nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your core engaged.</li>



<li>Avoid shrugging by keeping your shoulders down.</li>



<li>Make sure your elbows are pointed directly behind you – this targets your triceps more effectively.&nbsp;</li>



<li>When you push yourself back up, avoid locking your elbows as you extend your arms.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



